column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Very calm- sunny- mature ducks flying.
Water slightly wavy.  Storm + rain last night 1-7 a.m.  Overcast + misting.
Bright + sunny at time of testing.  2+" rain 4 days ago + drizzle since (following Florida hurricane).
Water was dark black. Overcast sky-slight breeze. Water very dark and stirred up. Numerous thunderstorms previous 12 hours. Dam still open + lake filling.
Bright sun. Moderate wave activity. Boat depth finder: 67'.
Cloudless sky. Water seems a little more brown this year.
This is the best test I've done yet! Sunny + calm.
Overcast- calm- dam is open and lake is rising.
Thin haze over sun.  Calm water.  This is one of the deepest readings I have been able to get.
Best reading was earlier this summer!
Very windy and wavy- causing rough water.  Limited depths for water sampling- a parent and one adult loon feeding on lake.
Rained hard on night previous to collection.  Breezy and wavy.  Hazy.
Cloudy windy wavy air temp 48 deg.
A gorgeous day!  Haven't seen any loons feeding in the evening@! ) :
Sunny with haze.  Very windy.  We couldn't get weight on water sampler to release the collection balls. Drifting   No water temperature below 3'
Windy- sunny and wavy. Worst secchi disk clarity reading of this year.
Perfectly calm and clear.  Can hear loons and can see mergansers fishing.
Bright sun- clear sky- windy- waves with white caps- and eagle soaring.
Windy- occasionally "white caps" on waves.  Baby loon still here.  Appears to be alone.  Adult migrate    Bright sun.
Single loon calling.  Bright sun.  Moderate waves and wind.
A beautiful day!  A pair of loons with two (2) chicks!  :)
Clear and 75 degrees.   Two adult loons and 2 babies.
Sunny/ two Loons were seen Sunny with a light wind
WEATHER WAS PARTLY CLOUDY AND 68 DEGREES.  SAW TW0 LOONS ON LITTLE STAR.  TWO BABY LOONS AND A MOTHER ON MANITOWISH LAKE ALONG WITH AN EAGLE.
Windy today- difficullty in getting lower water temps.
